{{Orphan|date=October 2017}}

'''Georg Statz''' (1894–1945) was a school teacher and [[taxonomist]] who published widely on [[fossil]] insects from the [[Oligocene]] [[Rott Formation]] of Germany ([https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fossillagerst%C3%A4tte_Rott Rott am Siebengbirge]). Known as the "Statz Collection", his fossils are reposited at the [[Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County]] and the [https://www.steinmann.uni-bonn.de/institut/bereiche/palaeontologie Institüt fur Paläontologie, Universität Bonn].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://research.nhm.org/ip/georg-statz/|title=Georg Statz|last=Hendy|first=Austin|date=August 30, 2017|website=Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County Invertebrate Paleontology (LACMIP)}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://research.nhm.org/ip/projects/fossil-insects-of-la/|title=Fossil Insects of LA {{!}} Invertebrate Paleontology @ NHM|website=research.nhm.org|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref>

