'''REG1''' is an [[anticoagulant|anticoagulation system]].
It involves inhibition of [[Factor IX]]a.<ref name="pmid20072947">{{cite journal |author=Becker RC, Chan MY |title=REG-1, a regimen comprising RB-006, a Factor IXa antagonist, and its oligonucleotide active control agent RB-007 for the potential treatment of arterial thrombosis |journal=Curr. Opin. Mol. Ther. |volume=11 |issue=6 |pages=707–15 |date=December 2009 |pmid=20072947 |doi= |url=}}</ref>
