'''Robert Milson Appleby''' (28 April 1922 in [[Denton, Greater Manchester|Denton]] - 8 February 2004 in [[Grimsby]]) was a British [[palaeontologist]].<ref name=tel>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1456284/Robert-Appleby.html |title=Robert Appleby Obituary |work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date=2004-03-08 |accessdate=2017-01-01 }}</ref>
Appleby developed the ''Analogue Video Reshaper'' which was used to compare the anatomical structure of fossilised Ichthyosaurs as well as match fingerprints  in criminal investigations.<ref name=tel />

